               <t:note>
                  <t:date type="foundation" notBefore="1300" notAfter="1400">1300-1400</t:date>
                  <t:desc type="foundation">Local tradition tells that the monastery was founded in the time of <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS1854Amdase">ʿAmda Ṣǝyon</t:persName> (r. <t:date>1318-1348</t:date>) by ʾabuna <t:persName type="tabot" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS1296Abreham">Abrǝhām (of Qata)</t:persName> 
                     (the founder of <t:placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0171KY">Koholo Yoḥannǝs</t:placeName>).</t:desc>
                  <t:ab type="history">Gadām. At least 10 monks resided in the monastery at the moment of the visit. 
                     A nunnery <t:placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC2910EndaMa">ʾƎndā Māḥṣun</t:placeName>, dedicated to <t:persName type="tabot" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6524Mahsanta">Māḥṣanta Māryām</t:persName>, is located further down the valley of river <t:placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC7208Gewa">Gǝwā</t:placeName>. 
                     Ruins of other structures (churches or dwellings of monks?) are visible along the river valley. 
                  </t:ab>
                  <t:ab type="tabot">Tābots: large unidentified number, including 
                     <t:persName type="tabot" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10618ZaraB">Zarʾa Buruk</t:persName>, <t:persName type="tabot" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6524Mahsanta">Māḥṣanta Māryām</t:persName>, <t:persName type="tabot" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS1296Abreham">Abrǝhām (of Qata)</t:persName> 
                     <t:ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/CovenantMercy">Kidāna Mǝḥrat</t:ref>, <t:persName type="tabot" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS9162TaklaHa">Takla Haymanot</t:persName>, <t:persName type="tabot" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6819Mary#Zion">Zion</t:persName> (?), 
                     <t:persName type="tabot" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6819Mary">Mary</t:persName>, <t:persName type="tabot" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10253Yasay">Yāsāy</t:persName>, <t:persName type="tabot" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS9982WaldaTe">Walda Tǝnśāʾe</t:persName> and others.</t:ab>
                  <t:ab type="description">
                     <t:figure>
                        <t:graphic url="Sites/MAKM.tif">
                           <t:desc>The church photographed by Denis Nosnitsin during the Ethio-SPaRe project.</t:desc>
                        </t:graphic>
                     </t:figure>
